highlights.text: “White Horse” by Chris Stapleton is the biggest gainer on Top Songs USA, up 138 spots at #45.
“No Role Modelz” by J. Cole has been on Top Songs USA the longest, at 182 weeks straight.
Taylor Swift has the most spots on Top Songs USA. “Is It Over Now? (Taylor's Version) (From The Vault)” is the highest at #1.
“Lovin On Me” by Jack Harlow is the highest new entry on Top Songs USA at #2.
